50|$|In finance, {{mortgage}} yield is {{a measure}} <b>of</b> <b>yield</b> <b>of</b> mortgage-backed <b>bonds.</b> It {{is also known as}} cash flow yield. The mortgage yield, or cash flow <b>yield,</b> <b>of</b> a mortgage-backed <b>bond</b> is the monthly compounded discount rate at which net present value of all future cash flows from the bond will be equal to the present price <b>of</b> the <b>bond.</b>|$|R
